content.description: A fun traverse line to a relatively high topout on good crimp rails. Begin the same as Biscuits on the lower right part of the rail. Traverse up and left to mantle out on the high point of the boulder. Top was cleaned July 2021 but may need some more cleaning in the future.
content.location: West face of the Brunch Boulder

content.description: Start on the lower rail feature either directly beneath the route or lower to the right if you want to add a few moves. Move up on edges to top out over a crack feature. Could use some more cleaning up, but rock quality is solid.
content.location: Middle of the West face of Brunch Boulder.

content.description: A large boulder with multiple faces of quality rock. The West face consists of parallel rails while the East face is featured with slots and jugs. This boulder likely has an established name, so please comment and update as needed.
